# Custom Tools Directory

This directory is for user-defined custom tools.

Each tool should:
1. Extend the BaseTool class from ../lib/baseTool.js
2. Be saved as a .js file
3. Export the tool class as the default export

Example tool structure:
```javascript
const BaseTool = require('../lib/baseTool');

class MyCustomTool extends BaseTool {
  constructor(context) {
    super(context);
    this.name = 'myTool';
    this.description = 'My custom tool description';
    // ... other properties
  }

  async execute(params, messageData) {
    // Tool implementation
  }
}

module.exports = MyCustomTool;
```

The tools will be automatically loaded at startup and can be hot-reloaded in development mode.